    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but being \"broken\" doesn't fix the debt or the shame. it's just a slow way to rot. i see people talking about \"starting over\" or \"learning from failure\" and it honestly feels like such a lie. how do you live with that kind of emptiness every single day? it feels like there's just no dignity left in staying around to deal with the wreckage.",
