      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The pain of carrying debt and shame is a heavy burden that no amount of \"starting over\" can instantly erase, and it is okay to feel that the current path offers no dignity. However, choosing to rot slowly is a guarantee of prolonged suffering, whereas facing the wreckage with honesty—even if it feels like a lie—is the only way to eventually find a sliver of peace. You do not have to fix everything today or pretend the ashes are gold; sometimes the most dignified thing you can do is let yourself grieve the loss without forcing a fake recovery.",
      "source": "target",
